{
  "id": "ex_technical_b5162bdc",
  "intent": "Perform automated viral RNA isolation using magnetic bead purification on up to 96 samples. Add 300\u00b5L ethanol and 50\u00b5L magnetic beads to samples, incubate off-magnet for 5 minutes then on-magnet for 2 minutes. Remove supernatant and perform three sequential wash steps with 680\u00b5L, 340\u00b5L, and 340\u00b5L wash buffers, each followed by 2-minute magnetic separation. Air dry beads for 10 minutes, elute with 25\u00b5L buffer for 4 minutes off-magnet, then transfer 4\u00b5L purified RNA to chilled 384-well elution plate. Include negative and positive controls in designated wells.",
